-- Inter Milan Striker Samuel Eto'o Banned for Three Matches After Headbutt
-- B y   D a n   L i e f g r e e n
-- 2010-11-23T11:14:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/inter-milan-striker-samuel-eto-o-banned-for-three-matches-after-headbutt.html
Inter Milan striker  Samuel Eto ’o was
banned for three matches after headbutting a Chievo defender in
a Nov. 21 Serie A match, his club said in a statement on its
website.  Inter said it will appeal the decision by the Italian
sports judge, who reviewed films of the match won by Chievo 2-1.
Eto’o also was fined 30,000 euros ($40,700) for the headbutt on
Chievo’s Bostjan Cesar.  Defending champion Inter is in sixth place in soccer’s
Serie A, nine points behind leader AC Milan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at  at
 celser@bloomberg.net  